HEADWORD: Setterwort
<hw>Set"ter*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The bear's-foot (<spn>Helleborus f⟦oe⟧tidus</spn>); -- so called
because the root was used in <xex>settering</xex>, or inserting setons
into the dewlaps of cattle. Called also
<altname>pegroots</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Dr. Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Setting</ent>⟦br⟧
